com.sap.conn.idoc

Interface IDocXMLProcessor


  • public interface IDocXMLProcessor
    General interface offering functionality for parsing and rendering IDoc-XML data.

      • PARSE_IGNORE_INVALID_CHAR_ERRORS

        static final int PARSE_IGNORE_INVALID_CHAR_ERRORS
        Parsing option for ignoring character range check errors in accordance with the declared XML specification version.
        If using this option invalid characters within field values are accepted although the XML document to parse may not be well-formed because it potentially contains characters not being in the valid character range.
        Since:
        IDocLibrary 3.0.9
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PARSE_WITHOUT_FIELD_DATATYPE_CHECKING

        static final int PARSE_WITHOUT_FIELD_DATATYPE_CHECKING
        Parsing option for disabling the field datatype checking mechanism in accordance with the respective IDoc field metadata.

        Caution: This option should be used with care. Sending IDocs with illegal field contents that are violating the field's defined datatype may cause ABAP system dumps and result in unrecognized partial loss of data when later being processed in an AS ABAP system.

        Since:
        IDocLibrary 3.0.11
        See Also:

      • RENDER_IGNORE_INVALID_CHAR_ERRORS

        static final int RENDER_IGNORE_INVALID_CHAR_ERRORS
        Rendering option for ignoring character range check errors in accordance with the used XML specification version.
        If using this option invalid characters within field values may also be rendered thus potentially resulting in not well-formed XML documents. The original IDoc content data is always kept in the rendered IDoc-XML document.
        Since:
        IDocLibrary 3.0.9
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • RENDER_SUBSTITUTE_INVALID_CHARS

        static final int RENDER_SUBSTITUTE_INVALID_CHARS
        Rendering option for substituting invalid characters within IDoc field values with the number sign '#' (U+0023). The valid character range is defined by the used XML specification version.
        This option takes precedence over option RENDER_IGNORE_INVALID_CHAR_ERRORS.

        Caution: If using this option the field values of the rendered IDoc-XML documents may differ from the original IDoc content data because of potentially substituted characters. This option is meant to be used in very special and rare use case scenarios only and usually should be avoided. Modifying and correcting the original business application data in the IDoc source system should always be preferred over using this option.

        Since:
        IDocLibrary 3.0.9
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • parse

        IDocDocumentList parse(IDocRepository repository,
                       String xmlString)
                throws IDocParseException
        Parses the given IDoc-XML string and creates a corresponding IDocDocumentList instance using the specified repository. The IDoc-XML format of the given XML string will be automatically detected.
        Parameters:
        repository - the repository to be used for querying the needed IDoc metadata information in order to create the corresponding IDocDocumentList instance.
        xmlString - the IDoc-XML string to be parsed.
        Returns:
        the IDocDocumentList instance created from the given IDoc-XML string.
        Throws:
        IDocParseException - if some error was detected when parsing the given IDoc-XML string.

                       String xmlString,
                       IDocXMLFormat format)

        Parses the given IDoc-XML string and creates a corresponding IDocDocumentList instance using the specified repository. The XML string is assumed to be of the specified IDoc-XML format.

      • parse

        IDocDocumentList parse(IDocRepository repository,
                       String xmlString,
                       int options)
                throws IDocParseException
        Parses the given IDoc-XML string and creates a corresponding IDocDocumentList instance using the specified repository and parsing options. The IDoc-XML format of the given XML string will be automatically detected.
        Parameters:
        repository - the repository to be used for querying the needed IDoc metadata information in order to create the corresponding IDocDocumentList instance.
        xmlString - the IDoc-XML string to be parsed.
        options - the special options for parsing the given IDoc-XML string. Multiple IDocXMLProcessor.PARSE_* options can be combined using the bitwise OR operator '|'.
        Note: The parse option PARSE_IGNORE_UNKNOWN_FIELDS is useful, if you expect to parse arbitrary versions.
        Returns:
        the IDocDocumentList instance created from the given IDoc-XML string.
        Throws:
        IDocParseException - if some error was detected when parsing the given IDoc-XML string.

      • parse

        IDocDocumentList parse(IDocRepository repository,
                       String xmlString,
                       int options,
                       String systemRelease,
                       String applicationRelease)
                throws IDocParseException
        Parses the given IDoc-XML string and creates a corresponding IDocDocumentList instance using the specified repository and parsing options. The IDoc-XML format of the given XML string will be automatically detected.
        Parameters:
        repository - the repository to be used for querying the needed IDoc metadata information in order to create the corresponding IDocDocumentList instance.
        xmlString - the IDoc-XML string to be parsed.
        options - the special options for parsing the given IDoc-XML string. Multiple IDocXMLProcessor.PARSE_* options can be combined using the bitwise OR operator '|'.
        Note: The parse option PARSE_IGNORE_UNKNOWN_FIELDS is useful, if you expect to parse arbitrary versions.
        systemRelease - the system release the resulting IDocDocumentList shall belong to, if null or an empty string is provided the latest available release will be used.
        applicationRelease - the application release the resulting IDocDocumentList shall belong to, if null or an empty string is provided the latest available release will be used.
        Returns:
        the IDocDocumentList instance created from the given IDoc-XML string restricted to the given release information.
        Throws:
        IDocParseException - if some error was detected when parsing the given IDoc-XML string.
        Since:
        IDocLibrary 3.0.5

      • parse

        IDocDocumentList parse(IDocRepository repository,
                       InputStream xmlStream)
                throws IOException,
                       IDocParseException
        Parses the IDoc-XML data obtained from the given XML input stream and creates a corresponding IDocDocumentList instance using the specified repository. The appropriate character encoding will be detected automatically and/or read from the XML encoding declaration obtained from the XML input stream. The IDoc-XML format of the XML data obtained from the given XML input stream will be automatically detected.
        Parameters:

        options - the special options for rendering the given IDocDocumentList. Multiple IDocXMLProcessor.RENDER_* options can be combined using the bitwise OR operator '|'.
        Returns:
        the IDoc-XML string.

      • render

        String render(IDocDocumentList iDocList,
              IDocXMLFormat format,
              String encoding,
              int options)
        Renders the given IDocDocumentList into an IDoc-XML string with the given IDoc-XML format and rendering options. By default the returned IDoc-XML string will contain an XML declaration section with the specified encoding attribute value.
        Parameters:
        iDocList - the IDocDocumentList to be rendered into an XML string.
        format - the IDoc-XML format of the XML string to be returned.
        encoding - the encoding attribute value for the XML declaration section.
        options - the special options for rendering the given IDocDocumentList. Multiple IDocXMLProcessor.RENDER_* options can be combined using the bitwise OR operator '|'.
        Returns:
        the IDoc-XML string.

      • render

        void render(IDocDocumentList iDocList,
            Writer xmlWriter)
     throws IOException
        Renders the given IDocDocumentList into an IDoc-XML string with the latest IDoc-XML format and writes it to the specified XML writer. The rendered IDoc-XML string will contain an XML declaration section either without an encoding attribute or with a mandatory encoding attribute value if it can be queried from the XML writer object (only if it is an instance of java.io.OutputStreamWriter).
        Parameters:
        iDocList - the IDocDocumentList to be rendered into an XML string.
        xmlWriter - the writer with which the rendered IDoc-XML string will be written.
        Throws:
        IOException - if some IO error occurred when writing to the given XML writer.
